- undefined symbo rp_app_init --> restart
- compiler plugin to short --> copy arm compiler again to the project.. Dont know why but seems like different linux distros are not working well together.

install new libsigrok:
remove old version
- apt remove libsigrokdecode-dev libsigrokdecode2
- install autoconf 'apt install autoconf'
- install automake 'apt install automake'
- install libtool 'apt install libtool'
- install libzip 'apt install libzip-dev'

for c++ bindings
- install glibmm-2.4 'apt install libglibmm-2.4-dev'
- install doxygen 'apt install doxygen'
- the other necessary packages should be installed already.
- https://sigrok.org/wiki/Building#Build_requirements

- install the libsigrok decoder finally

- link the new shared object. 
- cd /etc/ld.so.conf.d
- create new file like 'libsigrok.conf' or something similar
- add the path of the installed libsigrokdecode.so to the file.
- run 'ldconfig' to refresh the settings

